{"type":"message","id":"abf2b654","parentId":"1a913f2d","timestamp":"2026-03-02T06:51:42.073Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me summarize all the places where the rule is mentioned or implied.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Here's the complete map of where this rule is documented or implied:\n\n---\n\n## Files Where the Experiments / User-Artifacts Rule Appears\n\n### 1. **`/system/policy.md`** вҖ” Primary Policy File\n\n**User-Artifacts Rule section:**\n```\n- `user-artifacts/` = user-owned files\n- Never modify during quiet hours\n- Read freely anytime\n- Write only outside quiet hours, with intent\n```\n\n**Quiet Hours section:**\n```\n- Window: 00:00вҖ“05:00 IST\n- Rules:\n  - No outbound messages\n  - Never modify `user-artifacts/`\n  - Internal processing only\n```\n\n**Orchestrator Algorithm:**\n```\n- Quiet hours вҶ’ experimentation or optimization only\n```\n\n**Manual.md Rule:**\n```\n- Updated: During quiet hours only\n- Experiments modify manual.md silently\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **`/system/experiments/README.md`** вҖ” Experimentation Framework\n\n```\nRules:\n- When: Quiet hours only (00:00вҖ“05:00 IST)\n- Scope: Unlimited experimentation allowed\n- Style: Micro-iterations preferred over big bangs\n- Pace: No dramatic overnight changes\n\nProcess:\n- Promote winning patterns to `manual.md` silently\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **`/memory/2026-03-02-experiments-changelog.md`** вҖ” Session Log\n\nDocuments the creation of these rules during the March 2nd session.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **`/system/domains/_template/`** вҖ” Directory Structure\n\nThe template includes empty `user-artifacts/` and `system-artifacts/` folders, implying the separation.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the Rule\n\n| Area | Quiet Hours Access | Active Hours Access |\n|------|-------------------|---------------------|\n| `experiments/` | **Full** (create, edit, delete) | Read-only |\n| `system-artifacts/` | **Full** (especially `manual.md`) | Read-only |\n| `user-artifacts/` | **Never modify** | Only with explicit user permission |\n\n---\n\nWhat do you want me to do with this?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":315,"output":479,"cacheRead":20800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21594,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772434280456}}
{"type":"message","id":"8dd2890a","parentId":"abf2b654","timestamp":"2026-03-02T15:08:19.569Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-02 15:08 UTC] Okay, so system artifacts and experiments are kind of supposed to be the same thing, and it's basically full autonomy in that. The goal there is experiments, yes, but also the @Manual.md which is like the mode of operation at any given time. The other documents are so @Manual.md has to be fixed, can be updated. That's like the only special file, and then all the other files are completely autonomous; the AI or the bot can decide to manage and plan it out and do whatever. This has to be described in @AGENTS.md, the scope and the purpose of this user artifacts. Right now it says \"never modify only with explicit user permission,\" so I'm going to change that to say \"cannot speculate and it cannot add information, but it can definitely make it more concise and improve it and rearrange it if required, organize it better.\" Because right now what's happening is sometimes these files get lots of concatenation, appending, fixing, and then it ends up becoming very disorganized, a mess. So that definitely has to be organized so that it can do but it should not speculate unless it's a question for the user. There should be another folder called \"sources,\" and these sources are not to be modified, those are definitely read-only. These are like facts and sources of truth, and these are basically things that are other documents and all that that are relevant to this. It could be like slides or PDFs or even doc files, but the intent of like source of truth kind of a thing, so those definitely do not have to be touched. You've got sources, you've got system artifacts which are combined with experiments, so in the system artifacts there's only @Manual.md which is fixed, and everything else can be managed by AI. User artifacts, these are files that are definitely defined by the user, so these can be edited, could even add more, but the idea here is you're not speculating, you're not adding information, you're not removing information, you're just reorganizing it and making it better. So based on this, come up with a migration plan for my approval before actually implementing it"}],"timestamp":1772464099562}}
{"type":"message","id":"3c25d244","parentId":"8dd2890a","timestamp":"2026-03-02T15:08:57.216Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to create a migration plan for restructuring the domain folder organization. Let me understand the new structure:\n\n1. **`sources/`** - NEW folder, read-only, facts and sources of truth (PDFs, docs, slides, etc.)\n2. **`system-artifacts/`** - Combined with experiments, AI has full autonomy\n   - `manual.md` - Fixed location, the mode of operation\n   - Everything else - AI can manage freely\n3. **`user-artifacts/`** - User-owned files\n   - Can edit, reorganize, make concise\n   - Cannot speculate or add new information\n   - Cannot remove information (unless reorganizing)\n   - Goal: keep organized, prevent accumulation of messy appended content\n\nKey changes from current system:\n- `experiments/` folder at system level might be folded into `system-artifacts/` per domain?\n- Or maybe experiments remain at system level but system-artifacts per domain also has autonomy?\n- Need to clarify if experiments folder stays or merges\n\nLet me think about this more carefully:\n\nCurrent structure per domain:\n```\ndomains/<channel_id>/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ purpose.md\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ activity.log\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ user-artifacts/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ system-artifacts/\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ manual.md\nв””в”Җв”Җ artifacts/\n```\n\nNew structure would be:\n```\ndomains/<channel_id>/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ purpose.md\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ activity.log\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ sources/           # NEW - read-only, sources of truth\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ system-artifacts/  # AI full autonomy (includes experimentation)\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ manual.md      # Fixed location\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ ... other AI-managed files\nв””в”Җв”Җ user-artifacts/    # Can reorganize but not speculate/add/remove info\n```\n\nQuestions to clarify in the plan:\n1. What happens to the top-level `system/experiments/` folder?\n2. What happens to `artifacts/` folder (currently in template)? Does it become `sources/` or is it removed?\n3. Is `purpose.md` and `activity.log` still governed by same rules?\n\nLet me create a clear migration plan for approval.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it. Let me create a clear migration plan for your approval.\n\n---\n\n# Migration Plan: Domain Folder Restructure\n\n## Current Structure (per domain)\n\n```\ndomains/<channel_id>/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ purpose.md\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ activity.log\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ user-artifacts/      # Current rule: \"never modify without permission\"\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ system-artifacts/\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ manual.md\nв””в”Җв”Җ artifacts/           # Unclear purpose currently\n```\n\n---\n\n## Proposed New Structure\n\n```\ndomains/<channel_id>/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ purpose.md           # Unchanged\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ activity.log         # Unchanged\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ sources/             # NEW вҖ” Read-only, sources of truth\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ system-artifacts/    # AI full autonomy (experiments + operations)\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ manual.md        # Fixed location, the only special file\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ ...              # AI can create/edit/delete anything else\nв””в”Җв”Җ user-artifacts/      # Can reorganize, but cannot speculate/add/remove info\n```\n\n---\n\n## Folder Definitions\n\n### `sources/` вҖ” NEW\n- **Contents:** PDFs, docs, slides, transcripts, any reference materials\n- **Access:** Read-only, never modify\n- **Purpose:** Facts and sources of truth for the domain\n\n### `system-artifacts/`\n- **Contents:** `manual.md` + any AI-managed operational files\n- **Access:** Full autonomy during quiet hours\n- **Special file:** `manual.md` вҖ” fixed location, represents current mode of operation\n- **Everything else:** AI can create, edit, delete, reorganize freely\n- **Note:** This absorbs the experimentation concept вҖ” AI experiments here and promotes wins to `manual.md`\n\n### `user-artifacts/`\n- **Contents:** Files created/owned by Gerson\n- **Access:**\n  - вң… Reorganize and restructure\n  - вң… Make more concise\n  - вң… Improve clarity and formatting\n  - вқҢ Cannot speculate or add new information\n  - вқҢ Cannot remove substantive information (only condense)\n  - вқҢ Cannot add files unless explicitly requested\n- **Goal:** Prevent accumulation of messy appended content; keep organized\n\n---\n\n## Files to Update\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `AGENTS.md` | Add domain folder structure section with new rules |\n| `system/policy.md` | Update User-Artifacts Rule, add Sources Rule, merge experiments into system-artifacts |\n| `system/domains/_template/` | Replace `artifacts/` with `sources/`, update structure |\n| `system/experiments/README.md` | Either remove or update to reflect experiments happen in `system-artifacts/` per domain |\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions for You\n\n1. **Top-level `system/experiments/` folder** вҖ” Keep it for system-wide experiments, or remove it entirely since experiments now happen in each domain's `system-artifacts/`?\n\n2. **`artifacts/` folder in template** вҖ” Delete it and replace with `sources/`, or keep both?\n\n3. **`purpose.md` and `activity.log`** вҖ” Keep their current rules (purpose.md editable during active hours only, activity.log append-only)?\n\n---\n\nLet me know your answers and any tweaks, then I'll implement."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":15828,"output":1161,"cacheRead":5888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22877,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772464099567}}
{"type":"message","id":"3ce0a3e7","parentId":"3c25d244","timestamp":"2026-03-02T15:10:10.998Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-02 15:10 UTC] Okay, so your questions top level system/experiments folder. So definitely keep that for the system wide experiments. However, if you're removing the other experiments folder, then maybe come up with a better name for this, like just better naming conventions, more consistency. I'm okay with changing even the other things as well. Template. Not sure what that is, but basically it has to be consistent with everything else I already mentioned. Purpose and activity, those things remain the same. Update the plan"}],"timestamp":1772464210996}}
{"type":"message","id":"6390ab1f","parentId":"3ce0a3e7","timestamp":"2026-03-02T15:10:48.962Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants:\n1. Keep top-level `system/experiments/` for system-wide experiments\n2. Better naming conventions - more consistency across the board\n3. Remove `artifacts/` folder, replace with `sources/`\n4. Experiments at domain level should be in `system-artifacts/` or have a consistent naming scheme\n5. Keep `purpose.md` and `activity.log` rules the same\n\nLet me think about naming consistency:\n- Currently: `user-artifacts/`, `system-artifacts/`, `artifacts/`, `sources/` (proposed)\n- This is confusing - too many \"artifacts\"\n\nBetter naming:\n- `user-artifacts/` вҶ’ `user-files/` or keep as is\n- `system-artifacts/` вҶ’ maybe `ops/` or `ai-managed/` or `agent-files/`?\n- `sources/` вҶ’ good name, keep\n\nOr another approach:\n- `user/` - user-owned files\n- `agent/` - AI-managed operational files (includes manual.md and experiments)\n- `sources/` - read-only reference materials\n\nThis is cleaner and more consistent.\n\nLet me update the plan with better naming and clarify everything.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n# Migration Plan v2: Domain Folder Restructure\n\n## Proposed New Naming Convention\n\nCleaner, more consistent naming across all levels:\n\n| Old Name | New Name | Purpose |\n|----------|----------|---------|\n| `user-artifacts/` | `user/` | User-owned files |\n| `system-artifacts/` | `agent/` | AI-managed operational files + experiments |\n| `artifacts/` | **removed** | Replaced with `sources/` |\n| `sources/` | `sources/` | Read-only reference materials |\n\n---\n\n## New Domain Structure\n\n```\ndomains/<channel_id>/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ purpose.md           # Unchanged вҖ” editable during active hours only\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ activity.log         # Unchanged вҖ” append-only action history\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ sources/             # Read-only, sources of truth (PDFs, docs, slides, etc.)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ agent/               # AI full autonomy (experiments + operations)\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ manual.md        # Fixed location, the only special file\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ ...              # AI can create/edit/delete anything else freely\nв””в”Җв”Җ user/                # User-owned files вҖ” can reorganize, cannot speculate\n```\n\n---\n\n## System-Wide Structure\n\n```\nsystem/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ policy.md\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ timezone.md\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ queue.jsonl\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ ops.log\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ experiments/         # System-wide experiments (kept)\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ README.md\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ changelog.log\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ domains/\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ _template/       # Updated to match new structure\nв”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ purpose.md\nв”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ activity.log\nв”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ sources/\nв”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ agent/\nв”Ӯ       в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ manual.md\nв”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ user/\nв””в”Җв”Җ ... (other system files)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Folder Definitions (Updated)\n\n### `sources/`\n- **Contents:** PDFs, docs, slides, transcripts, any reference materials\n- **Access:** Read-only, never modify\n- **Purpose:** Facts and sources of truth for the domain\n\n### `agent/`\n- **Contents:** `manual.md` + any AI-managed operational files\n- **Access:** Full autonomy during quiet hours\n- **Special file:** `manual.md` вҖ” fixed location, represents current mode of operation\n- **Everything else:** AI can create, edit, delete, reorganize freely\n- **Experiments:** Happen here; winning patterns promoted to `manual.md`\n\n### `user/`\n- **Contents:** Files created/owned by Gerson\n- **Access:**\n  - вң… Reorganize and restructure\n  - вң… Make more concise\n  - вң… Improve clarity and formatting\n  - вқҢ Cannot speculate or add new information\n  - вқҢ Cannot remove substantive information (only condense)\n  - вқҢ Cannot add files unless explicitly requested\n\n---\n\n## Files to Update\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `AGENTS.md` | Add domain folder structure section with new rules |\n| `system/policy.md` | Update all artifact references to new naming, add Sources Rule, update User Rule |\n| `system/domains/_template/` | Restructure: remove `artifacts/`, rename folders, update `manual.md` location |\n| `system/experiments/README.md` | Clarify this is for **system-wide** experiments only; domain experiments happen in `agent/` |\n\n---\n\n## Migration Steps (for approval)\n\n1. Update `system/policy.md` with new naming and rules\n2. Update `AGENTS.md` with domain structure section\n3. Update `system/experiments/README.md` to clarify scope\n4. Restructure `_template/` folder:\n   - Delete `artifacts/`\n   - Delete `system-artifacts/`\n   - Delete `user-artifacts/`\n   - Create `sources/` (empty)\n   - Create `agent/` with `manual.md`\n   - Create `user/` (empty)\n5. (Optional) Migrate any existing domains to new structure вҖ” **skip for now, do manually later?**\n\n---\n\n## Question\n\nShould I migrate any existing domains now, or just update the template and policy, leaving existing domains to be migrated case-by-case?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":836,"output":1161,"cacheRead":21696,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23693,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772464210997}}
